This is another experience that I am sharing with you people. I hope you will like it. ( My visit to Kulang Fort 🌄)
•
🍃The fort is located at an elevation of about 4825 feet in the Igatpuri region of Nashik and is one of the oldest forts in the region as its history dates back to the era of the Satavahana dynasty.

🍃It is believed that the fort was constructed during the Common Era by the later kings of the Satavahanas.

🍃However, it was captured by several other rulers after the disestablishment of the dynasty. As per historical records, the fort has been under the reign of the Mughals, the Marathas, and later on, the British Army.

🍃Today, the fort is lying in its ruins and has become a weekend destination for trekkers and campers.

51rnW6WDXEw.title: KOTHALIGAD TREK⛰️🍁(PETH FORT)| Best Trekking Place near Mumbai | EASY-MODERATE LEVEL TREK - VLOG 11
51rnW6WDXEw.description:

Kem Cho😎,
This is another experience that I am sharing with you people. I hope you will like it. ( MY VISIT TO KOTHALIGAD/KOTHLIGAD FORT TREK 🌄)
.
Kothaligad, also known as Peth fort, rises to a maximum altitude of 3,033 ft approx. and was primarily used as a watchtower & ammunition depot by the ruling armies. The strategic location of the hill provides a commanding view of Padargad, Malanggad, Siddhagad, Chanderi fort, Bhimashankar & Matheran plateau in clear weather.

Located less than 100 km from both Mumbai and Pune and well connected by road and railways, Kothaligad is the ideal all-season trek for anyone looking for a quick getaway from the bustling city life.
.
*Highlights of the trek*😍
-------------------------------------------------------
✅ The unique thumb-like structure of the fort
✅ TWell preserved cannons from the fort’s heydays
✅ A panoramic view of the surrounding ranges🌳🛤
✅ The gushing waterfalls, often sent upwards by strong winds from the valley
✅ Intricately carved pillars in the cave temple.😇
.

MNXs146N83M.title: Tahuli Peak Trek | Best Trekking Place near Mumbai | Moderately Difficult LEVEL TREK - VLOG 9
MNXs146N83M.description:
Hello Friends,
This is another experience that I am sharing with you people. I hope you will like it. (MY VISIT TO TAHULI PEAK)
.
Information about TAHULI PEAK:
---------------------------------------------------------
1. Tahuli is not one of the spots which are not very crowded, that's what makes it even more beautiful. Not many people know about this location, so it is less explored.

2. The places near Tahuli are very crowded amongst trekkers. So, if you are looking forward to peaceful trekking then you can always trek at this location.

3. Tahuli is misunderstood as a fort but, actually, Tahuli Mountain contains pinnacles.

4. Tahuli comes under the region of Kajrat, Panvel, and Kalyan. If you want to challenge your trekking skills, then you can always reach to highest pinnacles of Tahuli. There are three famous pinnacles in Tahuli and the highest one is the most challenging one.


ATTRACTION around TAHULI :
----------------------------------------------------
While trekking through Tahuli Mountain you can always derive the pleasure to see the Ashram of Gaadge Baba Maharaj.

The mesmerizing beauty of the uppermost part of the plateau known as "Dadimaa Tahuli" is a must-see thing. There you can see five Islamic holy places and a small house opposite to it. After two hours of sweaty trekking; you will reach the base of pinnacles, one known as 'Daood' and the other as 'Baman'.

The Tahuli mountain ranges are surrounded by green lush, dense forests. And the trekkers cannot avoid the scenic beauty of beautiful green carpet while walking between the flowers on the walkway.

If you are a nature lover then the mountains of Tahuli will give you an awesome experience of nature. In your visit to Tahuli, go to Shree Malang fort, Chanderi fort, Mhaismaal for sure.

The beautiful waterfalls and expert trekking guidance double up the fun. Trekkers have always loved clicking the pictures sitting or lying in the laps of nature.
.
.

After two hours of sweaty trekking; you will reach the base of pinnacles, one known as 'Daood' and the other as 'Baman'.

The Tahuli mountain ranges are surrounded by green lush, dense forests. And the trekkers cannot avoid the scenic beauty of beautiful green carpet while walking between the flowers on the walkway.

If you are a nature lover then the mountains of Tahuli will give you an awesome experience of nature. In your visit to Tahuli, go to Shree Malang fort, Chanderi fort, Mhaismaal for sure.

The beautiful waterfalls and expert trekking guidance double up the fun. Trekkers have always loved clicking the pictures sitting or lying in the laps of nature.

a1NuOScKPTs.description:
This is my second vlog on my last trek of 2020, to the top of Maharashtra. Kalsubai at 5400ft is the highest peak of Maharashtra and this is the main reason for its popularity and difficulty. It is located in the Kalsubai mountain range which is an offshoot range from the main Sahyadri range.
.
Why Kalsubai should be your next trekking destination?
Surrounded by lush green forests and fields, the trekking route towards Maharashtra's Highest Peak is a surreal experience for all nature lovers and trek enthusiasts. Challenging yet fun-filled, trek towards the highest summit will test your patience and offer an amazing panoramic view of several more mountain ranges like Alang, Madangad, Kulang, Ratangad (south-west), and to the south Pabhargad, Ghanchakkar & Harishchandragad. Also, attempting to climb the most wish-listed mountain in the Sahyadri offers a great sense of achievement for most of the trekking enthusiasts.
.
